      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If your soil test confirms a nitrogen deficiency, you can fix it by adding organic matter like composted manure or fish emulsion to gently boost nutrient levels. Avoid heavy chemical nitrates right now, as rapid fertilization can shock young tomato plants, so mix these amendments into the soil during your weekly watering routine instead. Keep in mind that many tomato varieties naturally shift nutrients from older leaves to support fruit, so over-correcting before confirming the soil issue might actually stress the plant.",
